Department / Job Category: Computer and Information Technology
Last Date: 30 May, 2014
Salary: 40000
Relevant Experience:
2 to 3 years of relevant experience
Job Description:
Identify potential areas of compliance vulnerability and risk; develop/implement corrective active plan for problematic issues and provide general guidance to other IT operations people on how to avoid/deal with similar situations in the future.
Monitor the performance of the IT functions on compliance status and relates activities on a continuing basis, taking appropriate steps to improve its effectiveness.
Ensure the testing and quality assurance of the software/documentation artifacts as per prevailing standards.
Take part in the translation of the requirements/use cases into test cases.
Liaison with development and MIS team during the software development life.
Acquire/enhance task management/priority setting and effective coordination capabilities.
